<p class="p">The ERFs we used (
 <xref rid="c4" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">Baccini et al. 2008</xref>) required daily maximum apparent temperature (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M22" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">A</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">max</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>), which was computed as follows: 
 <disp-formula id="d1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">
   <span xml:space="preserve" class="x" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">[</span>1
   <span xml:space="preserve" class="x" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">]</span>
  </label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="EHP634_d1.jpg" position="float" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M23" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">A</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">max</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     <mn class="mn">2.653</mn>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mn class="mn">0.994</mn>
     <mo class="mo">×</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">max</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mn class="mn">0.0153</mn>
     <mo class="mo">×</mo>
     <msup class="msup">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mo class="mo">(</mo>
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">t</mi>
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">d</mi>
        </msub>
        <mo class="mo">)</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </msup>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M24" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">d</mi>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the daily mean dew point computed from 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M25" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">R</mi>
    <mi class="mi">H</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M26" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">mean</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> following the method described by Tetens (
 <xref rid="c53" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">1930</xref>). For Barcelona, the daily mean apparent temperature (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M27" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">A</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">mean</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>) had to be calculated because the ERF for Barcelona required this instead of 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M28" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">A</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">max</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. Therefore, we calculated daily 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M29" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">A</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">T</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">mean</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> by replacing 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M30" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">max</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> with 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="M31" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mtext class="mtext">mean</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> in 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="d1" class="xref">Equation 1</xref>.
</p>
